package {{.PackageName}}

// Parser scaffolding for {{.DisplayName}}.
//
// Every panel command Webox calls (create subdomain, create DB, list
// vhosts, …) gets its own parser here. Parsers are pure functions:
// raw bytes in, typed result out. Steps for each new parser:
//
//  1. Capture a golden fixture in testing/fixtures/{{.Name}}/ — see
//     the directory's README.md for sanitisation policy.
//  2. Add a table-driven entry to parsers_test.go: success +
//     known-error + malicious (ANSI / NUL / oversized) fixtures.
//  3. Implement the parser using `stripAndNormalize` + a named-group
//     regex. Return providers.ErrUnknownOutputFormat for unrecognised
//     shapes; never include raw secret bytes in the error.
//  4. Wire the parser into the method in provider.go.
//
// See providers/smallhost/parsers.go for the canonical reference.
